"&#xa0;\nWritten evidence submitted by AES Southern LtdDeclaration of interestAES Southern Ltd \nare a leading sustainability company providing consultancy and assessment services to the new build domestic market in relation to the Code for Sustainable Homes and are accredited to do so with both the BRE and STROMA\nAES Southern Ltd              \n&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; \nAES Southern Ltd \nwas established in 2005 as a direct \nresponse to demand from developers for independent, practical advice \non delivering sustainable developments in line with current and future regulations, \nwhich they could rely on. Keeping this at the heart of everything we do, AES Southern has grown to become a leading sustainability consultancy to the new build industry in the UK. We work with a \nbroad \nrange of clients including top 10 UK developers, delivering an end to end service from pre-acquisition and planning advice to on-site post construction assessment and certification. \nOur portfolio of services to both\n residential an\nd non-residential developments include\n strategy documents, SAP, SBEM, \nCfSH\n, BREEAM, psi value calculations and overheating risk analysis.\n \n&#xa0;\n\n&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; \nWe are actively involved in a number of industry groups such as the HBF and Zero Carbon Hub, providing insight and responses \nbased on our knowledge and experience \nto key consultations\n. \nCurrently we are represented on 4 working groups advising the ZCH in regards to the Industry and government sponsored project on “Closing the gap between design and as-built performance”\n&#xa0;\n\n&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; \nOur highly experienced team of consultants shares a passion for developing their technical expertise \nwhilst promoting sustainable design\n. We engage with the wider industry to keep abreast of the issues that matter to our clients and make sure the advice we are giving is up to \ndate.\n Through our engagement with projects at an early stage we are able to propose energy and sustainability strategies that we know are deliverable. \nWe believe that the Code for sustainable homes has provided an excellent platform for driving sustainability in the built and associated environment, and by doing so, has been the catalyst for significant investment in technological advances and innovation as well as providing structure for developers, suppliers and manufacturers\nCommentsWhilst AES Southern\n \nunderstands and supports \nthe Government’s \naim \n\n&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; \nto simplify the current raft of  standards and regulations \n \n\n&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; \nto reduce bureaucracy and cost to developer\n\n&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; \nsupport growth whilst delivering quality, sustainability, safety and accessibility \n&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\n[Date]\n&#xa0;\n DCLG, Housing Standards Review, August 2013, Paragraph 31\n DCLG, Housing Standards Review, August 2013, Paragraph 27\n DCLG, Housing Standards Review, August 2013, Paragraph 231\n DCLG, Housing Standards Review, August 2013, Paragraph 232\n \nLGA response to draft National Planning Policy Framework\n,\n 17 October 2011\n National Planning Policy Framework, March 2012, paragraph 8\n \nLGA response to draft National Planning Policy Framework\n,\n 17 October 2011\n"